<cheatsheet
      title="Displaying properties">
   <intro>
      <description>
         Among others, <b>GraphWalker</b> offers 2 CLI (Commands line interface) commands which are : <br/>
         1 <b>methods</b>  <br/>
         2 <b>requirements</b><br/>
         In order to avoid you to have to leave your Eclipse environment to run a shell to execute them, 
         you will use a properties panel to display the execution results of them.<br/> 
		 More information on this at http://graphwalker.github.io/cli-methods/ and http://graphwalker.github.io/cli-requirements/
      </description>
   </intro>
   <item
         title="Displaying properties">
      <description>
             In the Package Explorer, right-click <b>SimpleImpl.json</b> and select <b>Properties</b>.	 <br/>
   			 In the left pane, select <b>GW4E</b>, <b>methods</b> and <b>requirements</b> are displayed. <br/>
     		 Click <b>Cancel</b><br/> 
     </description>
   </item>
</cheatsheet>
